    Problem walk‑through                                                        
                                                                                
     1 main() calls load_blob("abcdef").                                        
     2 Inside load_blob() the input string is longer than 4 characters, so the  
       recoverable‑error branch is taken (line 22‑25).                          
     3 That branch executes free(b->name); – the buffer that stores the name    
       is released – then it returns the same blob_t * to the caller while      
       leaving b->size set to 0.                                                
     4 Back in main() the code detects the error (b->size == 0) and prints a    
       message, but it still calls destroy_blob(b).                             
     5 destroy_blob() blindly does free(b->name); (line 33) and then free(b);   
       (line 34). Because b->name was already freed in step 3, the second free  
       is a double free. The runtime aborts with “Deallocation of freed         
       memory”.                                                                 
                                                                                
    The core defect is mismatched ownership: load_blob() frees a resource that  
    the caller still believes it owns. When the caller later cleans up, it      
    frees the same memory again.                                                
                                                                                
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    Minimal local fix (single‑line change)                                      
                                                                                
    Add a NULL assignment after the early free(b->name) so the subsequent call  
    to destroy_blob() becomes a no‑op:                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
     /* program.c – line 23, inside load_blob() */                              
     if (strlen(name) > 4) {                                                    
         free(b->name);          /* release the name buffer */                  
         b->name = NULL;         /* <-- add this line */                        
         b->size = 0;                                                           
         return b;               /* hand the partially‑initialised blob back    
     */                                                                         
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Effect: destroy_blob() will free(NULL), which is safe, and then free(b).    
    The program no longer crashes. This fix is minimal and keeps the existing   
    return‑value semantics.                                                     
                                                                                
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    Thorough root‑cause fix (redesign)                                          
                                                                                
    A more robust design eliminates the partially‑initialized blob altogether:  
                                                                                
                                                                                
     /* program.c – revised load_blob */                                        
     static blob_t *load_blob(const char *name) {                               
         blob_t *b = malloc(sizeof(*b));                                        
         if (!b) abort();                                                       
         b->name = strdup(name);                                                
         if (!b->name) abort();                                                 
                                                                                
         /* Simulated recoverable parse error. */                               
         if (strlen(name) > 4) {                                                
             /* Clean up everything before returning NULL */                    
             free(b->name);                                                     
             free(b);                                                           
             return NULL;          /* signal error, do not return a             
     half‑initialized blob */                                                   
         }                                                                      
                                                                                
         b->size = strlen(name);                                                
         return b;                                                              
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    And adjust main() accordingly:                                              
                                                                                
                                                                                
     int main(void) {                                                           
         blob_t *b = load_blob("abcdef");   /* now returns NULL on error */     
         if (!b) {                                                              
             fprintf(stderr, "load_blob: failed to allocate blob\n");           
             return 1;                                                          
         }                                                                      
         destroy_blob(b);                 /* safe – b has not been              
     prematurely freed */                                                       
         printf("done\n");                                                      
         return 0;                                                              
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Effect: No memory is ever freed twice; error handling cleanly aborts the    
    allocation, and the caller only cleans up a fully‑owned object.             
                                                                                
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    Summary                                                                     
                                                                                
     • Root cause: load_blob() frees b->name on the error path but still        
       returns the same blob_t *. destroy_blob() later frees b->name again →    
       double free → crash.                                                     
     • Minimal fix: set b->name = NULL after freeing it so the double free is   
       avoided.                                                                 
     • Root‑cause fix: redesign the error handling to either return NULL or     
       avoid freeing resources that the caller still owns, ensuring single      
       ownership of each allocation.                                            
                                                                                
    Recommendation                                                              
                                                                                
    Apply the minimal fix by inserting b->name = NULL; after free(b->name); at  
    line 23 in program.c. For a long‑term, safer solution, refactor             
    load_blob() to return NULL on error and perform all necessary clean‑up      
    before returning, as shown above.                                           
                                                                                
                                                                                
